<h1>HTML is defined as:</h1>
<p style="text-align: justify; line-height: 1.5; color:#FF0000; font-size:30px;">
<i>
HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is the standard markup language used to create and
design web pages. It defines the structure and layout of a web page by using a variety of
tags and elements. HTML is one of the core technologies of the World Wide Web,
alongside CSS and JavaScript.
</i>
</p>
<h1>CSS is defined as:</h1>
<p style="text-align: justify; line-height: 1.5; color:#ED03FE; font-size:20px;">
CSS, which stands for Cascading Style Sheets is a language in web development that
enhances the presentation of HTML elements. By applying styles like color, layout, and
spacing, CSS makes web pages visually appealing and responsive to various screen sizes.
</p>
